{"id": "EUVD-2022-55831", "enisaUuid": "ef270e07-ad99-3026-9068-ce035d43a894", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/msm/a6xx: Fix kvzalloc vs state_kcalloc usage\n\nadreno_show_object() is a trap!  It will re-allocate the pointer it is\npassed on first call, when the data is ascii85 encoded, using kvmalloc/\nkvfree().  Which means the data *passed* to it must be kvmalloc'd, ie.\nwe cannot use the state_kcalloc() helper.\n\nThis partially reverts commit ec8f1813bf8d (\"drm/msm/a6xx: Replace\nkcalloc() with kvzalloc()\"), but adds the missing kvfree() to fix the\nmemory leak that was present previously.  And adds a warning comment.\n\nPatchwork: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/507014/", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T15:30:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-30T15:30:28", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ecd63b2fbabc8fd6e5355c25fe1e186a74fa5272", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ec8f1813bf8d0737898f99a8c1c69df0cde0d7dd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4b1bbc0571a5d7ee10f754186dc3d619b9ced5c1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/83d18e9d9c0150d98dc24e3642ea93f5e245322c", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50867"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50867"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "13b4aa41-52b4-37ea-a0f6-741e4800be4d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b859f9b009bbfbc236d9b076c64c59ccb41b8737 <4b1bbc0571a5d7ee10f754186dc3d619b9ced5c1"}, {"id": "4538d90b-51f4-3367-9331-765c8208d03b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "542d72f8-635b-3945-ba55-da6c314cec3c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b859f9b009bbfbc236d9b076c64c59ccb41b8737 <ec8f1813bf8d0737898f99a8c1c69df0cde0d7dd"}, {"id": "79418ad5-30af-3e49-9d43-bf3ae1329859", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "7abcc194-12fe-3037-a3b6-d4ba7c8f514b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b859f9b009bbfbc